neighborhood_overview: The trendy and creative hub of Shoreditch hosts the best places to eat, drink and visit all within walking distance. Shoreditch accommodates some of London’s most cutting edge eateries and with culinary delights to suit all budgets. Check out Brick Lane, which continues to be a mecca for curry fans from all over the city and is a great way to spend an afternoon wandering around the vintage shops, trying the delicious street food and looking at street art. If you like shopping we recommend a trip to Blitz London - hailed as the biggest vintage shop in Europe! There is also the famous BoxPark here which is a little shopping area made from old shipping containers - great for shopping, eating and enjoying a drink in the evening! Additionally, make sure to take a trip to Columbia Road flower market on a Sunday, where this outdoor market is a great place to spend the morning strolling through the flower-adorned streets. Like movies and a killer view? Definitely spend an evening at the Roofto

host_about:
Hello! Welcome to my home. I’m a musician & music producer. Grown up in London & I’ve studied here in England at creative arts school the BRIT school & Jazz Honours Degree at Leeds College of Music. I have a real passion for the arts. 
I enjoy meeting people from all over the world and I enjoy showing others why I love living in Central London. I travel A LOT as a musician so I know what it’s like  - I really do enjoy hosting and use my own travel experience to make my hosting the best it can be :)

All the museums, live music venues, art galleries are just ride away from me as the Jubilee line is just a 2 minute walk from my home. I know a lot about London as I have been lucky enough to grow up here and been working in London in the music scene for 14 years now. 

Been lucky enough to travel the world myself as a touring musician & my favourite spots include North America, Sweden and Spain. I really do believe London is one of the best cities in Europe, and I’m glad I can offer my home up for others to enjoy the famous town!

I really do live by the principle " treat others as you’d like to be treated'. and all I ask is that whoever comes to stays, does the same! You’re more than welcome to come and stay in my apartment and enjoy all that London has to offer!

The space

In the property you will also find our glowing bedroom with a comfortable double bed and a full length mirror that opens up the room even more. The bathroom also comes with a toilet and walk in shower.

neighborhood_overview:
In Shoreditch, empty walls are future murals. The neighborhood’s industrial warehouses and dingy side streets offer plenty of potential space waiting to be reimagined. Old brick warehouses have transformed into interactive art galleries, and countless buildings have served as Banksy’s canvases. Shoreditch’s appeal as a creative playground stems (at least, in part) from an urban, gritty underbelly, but clean-cut treasures aren’t in short supply—Shoreditch’s design sensibilities also influence its trendy pubs and cafes.

A triangle of influences have made Shoreditch into one of London’s most distinctive and unusual areas. To the East, Bangla-town and Brick Lane – London’s celebrated curry mile – are a riot of smells and colours from the Indian subcontinent. In the West, the looming towers of Liverpool Street and the City represent the world’s most concentrated area of money-making talent, where a number of sophisticated business hotels have sprung up. host_about:
Love travelling, meeting locals and looking for unusual and authentic spot.

I am very respectful of other people spaces. On the other side I love hosting and be helpful to my guest because i know how it is to visit new places and how resourceful can be to have a generous host!
 
In general, I am not a big fun of too touristy places, especially if restaurant, always prefer the small and quirky situation where the locals love to go.
Love food, cooking and I am always keen to try new combinations and flavours. 
Very curious and a bit nerdy - when I can learn something new I get very excited! 
Passionate about music, jazz and blues but also electro and rock.
Easy going, clean and respectful of other people spaces.

Golden Rule: Treat others how you want to be treated!!

Summer 2020 only or long-term let! A luxury 3 double bed, two bathroom apartment on the 2nd floor of an Edwardian mansion block in Bloomsbury / Fitzrovia with concierge service and elevator. The apartment comprises an integrated open-plan designer kitchen, spacious lounge, built-in wardrobes, main bathroom (& shower), en-suite bathroom in master bedroom, a south-west sunny balcony, fluffy white towels, hotel toiletries, Krups coffee, & 100% 5 star reviews! All on the West End’s doorstep!

The space
It’s quite simply a fantastic, high spec, immaculately clean and quiet apartment right in the centre of London. Read our 100% 5 star reviews to get a real understanding of what previous guests have loved about the apartment. We will bend over backwards to make sure your stay in London is fun-filled and restful and that each day is followed by a comfortable and peaceful night’s sleep.

Guest access
Guests have access to the entire apartment property
neighborhood_overview: Our neighbourhood is, in my humble opinion, the best place to live in London (as confirmed by the Sunday Times which recently named it as such). The apartment is located on a quiet and tranquil residential street, but is on the doorstep of London's best shopping, restaurants, theatres and nightlife. Immediately to the east you have the beautiful and peaceful Bloomsbury squares; 10 minutes' walk south is the world famous Covent Garden and Soho for all your theatre and restaurant needs; directly to the west is trendy Fitzrovia with its excellent bars and restaurants; the vast array of Oxford Street & Regents Street shops are 10 minutes' walk to the south west; and to the north you've got the finest Royal park in London, Regents' Park, and London Zoo.
host_about:
Hi there, 

We’re a family of five who live in London and love experiencing everything it offers from theatres, restaurants, parks, shopping, museums etc etc etc. We lived in the apartment for 7 years and really made the most of the phenomenal experiences and attractions on the doorstep. It’s the best neighbourhood in central London and we miss it every day. 

Best wishes x

The apartment is situated in a predominantly residential area however some big-name neighbours reside pretty close. The Emirates Stadium (home of Arsenal Football Club) is just a 6-minute walk and the Metropolitan University is 4 minutes walk away. The closest underground station is a 1-minute stroll from the front door, Holloway Road Station is on the Piccadilly Line. A train from here will see you in Piccadilly Circus in less than 15 minutes.


Eating out
There is a fair choice of restaurants in walking distance from Greek, Ethiopian to European. Koutoukaki is only 4 minutes walk away serving a variety of Greek cuisine. Wolkite specializes in traditional Ethiopian dishes with vegetarian options, a no-frills restaurant with African motifs, it’s only 8 minutes. Three storey Town House. Kitchen and living room on the ground floor.. Four bedrooms and three bathrooms, two with full size showers, one with a shower over the bath. We keep one room for our use.. If we are using the house it will not be rented. Th
neighborhood_overview:
Quiet, with no passing traffic.. historically a military academy and arsenal.
The Royal Arsenal riverside is situated in Woolwich, Royal Borough of Greenwich. A very vibrant local scene.. with bars restaurants and cafes.. known locally to some as 'the campus'.. because of its young and trendy population and the architectural resemblance to a big redbrick/ ivy university.
host_about:
I live and work between London, Switzerland and France.. I have rented my houses in London for short stays since 2009, but through other sites.
I worked for a british airline for nearly 30 years. Now my wife, daughter and I share our time between Europe and the UK. My wife spends more time at our Chateau which is in France and also on Airbnb. I spend more time in Switzerland.
We enjoy travel, though we now travel mostly by car.. 
I am a great fan of historical buildings.. and have done a great deal of renovation both London and Europe.. the house on the site is in a very historically significant part of London.. the Hall we have especially so, though it isn’t available for rent.. as it used to be a main part of the Royal Academy of Science.
We have also spent a great deal of time restoring our chateau in France..
 
I can suggest many different things to do in London..not all of which involve going to Trafalgar Square or Oxford St and I have some great contacts.. Most of our trips always start on the Thames commuter boats.. London guides..people that will take you to a real football match.. chauferred cars for visiting.. and suggestions of the nearest golf courses.. 
None of which need to be ridiculously expensive..

I love cooking and wine.. hence some of the French attraction.. but London has some of the best to offer too..

Londons music and theatre is world renowned.. and its definately worth going to see something.. whether it is contemporary or classic.

What we have we keep.. but we are very happy to share it..

host_about:
Greetings from the Veeve team!


Veeve manage the largest collection of homes to rent for short stays in London since 2011, launching in Paris in 2017. Our rental homes are predominantly privately-owned, lived-in homes in vibrant neighbourhoods. Thanks to our fully managed service, when you stay in a Veeve property you can benefit from the spaciousness, personal style and relaxed feel of a home – but with all the amenities of a hotel.


Once a booking is confirmed our Customer Service team will become your main point of contact and get in touch with you to organise your arrival at the property (including airport transfers, upon request); after which our on-the-ground management team will look after all aspects of your stay, with in-stay support available to help with any queries.


We have strict cleanliness guidelines for our cleaners and all staff who enter our properties and have reinforced existing cleaning procedures in line with official WHO, British and French government guidance.


As always, our team ensure that all properties are cleaned to a professional standard before and after each stay, with increased focus on touch-point cleaning (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.).

 All staff who enter properties will follow the below procedures:
 

- Carry and regularly use alcohol-based hand rub
- Sanitise their mobile phones 
- Focus extra attention when cleaning key touch-point areas (door handles, kitchen surfaces, kettles, taps etc.)
- Wear protective gear where appropriate
- Wash and disinfect work shoes


We might be able to arrange for property viewings, upon request, for stays of over 28 nights. 


If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact us and we will be sure to answer you promptly.

neighborhood_overview: There’s a reason why so many films are set in Notting Hill. The neighbourhood’s cobblestoned streets weave through scrunched alleyways and richly furnished Victorian townhouses, and its stylish shops and passionate antique vendors satiate design-driven appetites—Notting Hill’s famed Portobello Road Market is a rummager’s delight. Celebrated as much for its idyllic streetscapes as it is for its cafe lifestyle and ephemeral fancies, it’s easy to understand Notting Hill's cinematic celebrity.
host_about: I'm British from Manchester,  England and I was living in the US for 10 years. I now have three places West London. My places are clean and clutter free. I am very into energy, spirituality, mediation so my place reflects that in a not-too-over-the-top kind of way. And I love interior design so hopefully  this is reflected too!  I furnished my places with Air bnb in mind since it works so well with my lifestyle. Love to travel myself and a very regular Airbnb user as a guest too - my favorite places are Bali, Belize, Sydney, India and Thailand if these places aren't on your list add them now! My house manager Steph helps me keep up with Airbnb - so you will have either me or Stephani available pretty much 24/7 if we host you to help you have the best time possible. Its only fun doing this if you and your family are having a great time on your trip.
